<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-04T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-04T15:00:00-05:00" n="151" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.01/2600: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-04T16:00:00-04:00">August 4,
                                    1943—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1430. For Murphy from the Under Secretary. The exchange of views between
                            ourselves and the British on the matter referred to in your 1349 of July
                            31 continue. Our formula was transmitted by the President to the Prime
                            Minister on July 22.<note n="13" xml:id="d151fn13">See telegram No. 321,
                                July 22, 12:25 p.m., from President Roosevelt to the British Prime
                                Minister, <ref target="#pg_175">p. 175</ref>.</note> An effort is
                            now <pb facs="0195" n="183" xml:id="pg_183"/> being made to expedite
                            agreement between the two Governments which we sincerely hope can be
                            accomplished in the near future. [Welles.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>